      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:p>To configure Safari for viewing your local <fr:link href="foreign-forester-tfmt-000R.xml" title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes" addr="//forester/tfmt-000R" type="local">forest</fr:link>, you must activate the <fr:em>Develop</fr:em> menu and then toggle one setting.</fr:p>
        <fr:ol><fr:li>Open Safari's settings window.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>In the <fr:em>Advanced</fr:em> tab, check the <fr:em>“Show Develop menu in menu bar”</fr:em> checkbox at the bottom.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Open the <fr:em>Develop</fr:em> menu in the menubar, and select <fr:em>“Disable Local File Restrictions”</fr:em>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
      </fr:mainmatter>
