              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p><fr:link href="foreign-forester-index.xml" title="Forester" addr="//forester/index" type="local">Forester</fr:link> renders your <fr:link href="foreign-forester-tfmt-000R.xml" title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes" addr="//forester/tfmt-000R" type="local">forest</fr:link> to some XML files in the <fr:code>output/</fr:code> directory; XML is, like HTML, a format for structured documents that can be displayed by web browsers. The <fr:link href="foreign-forester-tfmt-000R.xml" title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes" addr="//forester/tfmt-000R" type="local">forest</fr:link> template comes equipped with a built-in XSLT stylesheet (<fr:code>theme/default.xsl</fr:code>) which is used to instruct web browsers how to render your <fr:link href="foreign-forester-tfmt-000R.xml" title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes" addr="//forester/tfmt-000R" type="local">forest</fr:link> into a pleasing and readable format.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
